AI Synthesis AI026 Euroack Line
Interface User’s Manual
This is the Manual for the AI026 Eurorack Line Interface you can purchase it by going to:
https://aisynthesis.com/product/ai026-eurorack-line-interface/.
1. About the AI026 Eurorack Line Interface
The AI026 Eurorack Line Interface converts between +/- 2V Line Signals and +/- 5V Eurorack
signals. This allows for the best headroom and highest quality when processing Line signals with
Eurorack modules, and vice versa.
2. AI026 Controls
1. Line Level. This knob controls the
volume of Line Level Inputs. This
signal is at “unity” at approximately
3 o clock. Turning past 3 o'clock
will provide more gain for
non-normalized signals or for
saturation.
2. Euro Level. This knob controls the
volume of the Euro Level Inputs. It
is unity at fully CW.
3. Line Level In. These are stereo
inputs for Line Level Signals. The
Left is normalled to the Right, so
that when no cable is in the Right
Input, the left signal will be passed
to that input.
4. Euro Level In. These are stereo
inputs for EuroLevel Signals. The
Left is normalled to the Right, so

that when no cable is in the Right Input, the left signal will be passed to that input.
5. Line Level Out. These are Line Level Outputs of the Euro Level in signals.
5. EuroLevel Out. These are Euro Level Outputs of the Line In signals.
4. Power
The AI026 uses a shrouded header and reverse power protection to prevent the cable being plugged
in the wrong way. The unit draws 11 mA on the positive rail, and 11 mA on the negative side.
